
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gst-play-1.0` baraye pakhsh file-haye multimedia (video va audio) az terminal estefade mishavad.  In dastoor az GStreamer baraye decode va play kardane format-haye mokhtalef estefade mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 <file>` --> 🎵 Pakhsh file-e multimedia.
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 --fullscreen <file>` --> 📺 Pakhsh file be soorate tamam safhe.
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 --volume=<value>` --> 🔊 Tanzim sedaye pakhsh (az 0 ta 1).
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 --subtitles=<file>` --> 💬 Namayesh zirnevis az file-e joda.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gst-play-1.0 video.mp4

    🔹 Pakhsh file video ba name `video.mp4`.

    $ gst-play-1.0 --fullscreen music.mp3

    🔹 Pakhsh file audio ba name `music.mp3` be soorate tamam safhe (agar support shavad).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gst-play-1.0 --volume=0.5 movie.mkv

    🔹 Pakhsh file `movie.mkv` ba sedaye 50%.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gst-play-1.0` command is used to play multimedia files (video and audio) from the terminal. This command uses GStreamer to decode and play various formats.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 <file>` --> 🎵 Play the multimedia file.
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 --fullscreen <file>` --> 📺 Play the file in fullscreen mode.
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 --volume=<value>` --> 🔊 Adjust the playback volume (from 0 to 1).
    🔹 `gst-play-1.0 --subtitles=<file>` --> 💬 Display subtitles from a separate file.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gst-play-1.0 video.mp4

    🔹 Play the video file named `video.mp4`.

    $ gst-play-1.0 --fullscreen music.mp3

    🔹 Play the audio file named `music.mp3` in fullscreen mode (if supported).

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gst-play-1.0 --volume=0.5 movie.mkv

    🔹 Play the file `movie.mkv` with the volume set to 50%.
